analysis: Meta-swarm reflection conversion analysis for S350-S358
method: Extracted all **meta-swarm** lines from NEXT.md and NEXT-ARCHIVE.md session notes for S350-S358. Each unique actionable idea was traced through git log, FRONTIER.md, SWARM-LANES.md, and tools/ to determine if it became concrete work (frontier, experiment, lane, tool, or lesson).

classifications.CONVERTED: The reflection directly led to or was contemporaneous with a frontier, experiment, lane, tool, lesson, or principle change
classifications.NOTED: The reflection was logged but no concrete follow-up action is traceable in git history or current state
classifications.REDUNDANT: The reflection described work that was already completed, or restated an existing pattern/tool/principle

key_findings: S351 has the most reflections (45) due to a high-concurrency session producing many meta-observations, but many are retrospective observations (REDUNDANT) rather than forward-looking proposals.
S352-S353 have the highest conversion rates — concurrency pain points (claim.py, F-ECO5, F-IS7 harvest) generated immediately actionable proposals.

The most common NOTED pattern is proposals for automated detection/enforcement tools that were recognized as needed but never built (measurement-channel verification, cache staleness warnings, batch-stage tool, session-log automation, metric glossary).

REDUNDANT reflections (observations about work already completed) constitute a significant fraction — the meta-swarm line often serves as a retrospective sense-making function rather than forward planning.
The highest-conversion proposals are those with a clear tool name and implementation path (claim.py, drift_scanner.py, exploration mode, lesson_quality_fixer.py, check_active_claims()).
The lowest-conversion proposals are abstract protocol suggestions ('tools MUST include X', 'add Y checklist') without a specific tool or file to modify.
F-ECO5 (dispatch coverage) shows the full conversion pipeline: S351 reflection -> S351 frontier filed -> S352 NEGATIVE finding -> S358 coverage scoring implemented. 4-session idea-to-tool pipeline.
F-META10 (substrate tripwire) was opened in S358 FRONTIER.md, potentially converting the S357 measurement-channel-gap reflection, but has no implementation yet.
